# Shell Git Repository

This repository contains a collection of shell scripts that can be used for various purposes. Each script focuses on a specific task or functionality, providing a quick and efficient solution.

## Table of Contents

- [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Scripts](#scripts)
- [Contributing](#contributing)
- [License](#license)

## Installation

To use these shell scripts, follow the steps below:

1. Clone this repository to your local machine using the following command:
   ```shell
   git clone <repository_url>
   ```

2. Change into the cloned directory:
   ```shell
   cd shell-git-repo
   ```

3. Make the desired script executable by running the following command:
   ```shell
   chmod +x <script_name>.sh
   ```

## Usage

After completing the installation steps, you can run any script from the repository by executing the following command:
```shell
./<script_name>.sh
```

Make sure to replace `<script_name>` with the name of the script you want to execute.

